item.title: [ISS-197] Build error using DEVELOPMENT-SNAPSHOT-2016-06-06-a
item.description:
I'm attempting the PerfectTemplate example and there seems to be a new duplicate symbol error on the linux build.

  • Ubuntu 15.x
  • DEVELOPMENT-SNAPSHOT-2016-06-06-a
/home/cameron/Development/PerfectTemplate/.build/debug/PerfectLib.build/PerfectError.swift.o: multiple definition of 'linux_errno'
/usr/bin/ld.gold: /home/cameron/Development/PerfectTemplate/.build/debug/PerfectNet.build/Net.swift.o: previous definition here

Full log below.

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Kyle Jessup It would make sense for var errno: Int32... to live inside PerfectError.swift, which is a good place, except that other Perfect components shouldn't have to include Perfect lib just to use the error type. I'm sure there's a good place. (Sorry - I just started looking at Perfect yesterday. Still figuring this out)
It's building on all platforms now. Thanks!
